Bollente Companies, Inc.















































Bollente Companies, Inc.













 


 Partners in Growth 
Bollente Brings Value to Visionaries


Company Overview




 







We understand what entrepreneurs need to transform
great ideas into thriving companies.





At Bollente Companies, our passion is to partner with zealous entrepreneurs and provide guidance to seize growth opportunities and deliver unsurpassed value for shareholders.
With a foundation deeply rooted in growing innovative companies, the Bollente team offers hands-on collaborative direction. We specialize in refining strategic planning, exploring capitalization structures, pursuing accretive mergers or acquisitions, enhancing market presence and assistance in building qualified executive management teams.
 





Our Brands




 







Bollente Companies is growing a diverse portfolio of companies with an interest in disruptive technologies that positively impact the environment, consumer lifestyles, or emerging economies.






trutankless – Tankless Electric Water Heater
Introducing an innovation in water heating technology – trutankless. We’ve transformed the traditional, wasteful and bulky water heater into a sleek, space-saving tankless design that’s packed with cutting edge technology. Energy conservation and long term savings for you are what drive us, and our vision to use forward thinking technology to provide endless hot water for your entire home resulted in a product we’re very proud to offer. It’s a sophisticated solution that means something simple to you – endless hot water.
Visit the trutankless website.






Our Strategy

 



 







At Bollente, we are highly selective when identifying teams, markets, and business models. We pursue opportunities that can achieve rapid growth and strong profitability to generate lasting returns for our shareholders.











 

Disruptive Innovation

We are passionate about forward thinking technologies that make everyday life better for people and the environment.









 

Rapid Growth

We look for passionate people with great ideas that have the potential to achieve rapid growth and profit.









 

Active Management

We focus on companies that can leverage our experience and benefit from synergies with our operating subsidiaries.











Leadership




 


Leadership

The team at Bollente Companies hails from a diverse background. Collectively, the team has vast knowledge and experience in building public and private companies in the cleantech, web-enhanced services and premium consumer products sectors.


Robertson James Orr
President and CEO
Bollente Companies, Inc.

Robertson James Orr has served as President & CEO of Bollente Companies since May 2010.
An energetic serial entrepreneur, Mr. Orr brings a wealth of strategic business development knowledge and expertise to Bollente Companies. In 1998, Mr. Orr became a founding partner of bluemedia, Inc., one of the nation’s leading signage and large-format graphics companies headquartered in Tempe, Arizona. As the company’s Sr. Vice President of Sales and Business Development, Mr. Orr has led bluemedia’s impressive 28% annual growth rate and fostered the recent acquisition of Skyline Signs.
In 2005, Mr. Orr and his partners funded another venture, Blind Society, an award-winning advertising and branding agency in Scottsdale, Arizona. Blind Society boasts an impressive client roster which includes the Arizona Cardinals, AT&T, Phoenix Coyotes, Four Peaks Brewery, Warner Brothers, Pixar Entertainment and Mojo Yogurt.
Mr. Orr graduated from Arizona State University with a Bachelor of Arts degree in Business Management in 1997. A Cincinnati Ohio native, Mr. Orr is socially conscious and has supported non-profit organizations including Boys & Girls Club of Phoenix, St. Joseph the Worker, Muscular Dystrophy Association (MDA), Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA) and served on the Board of Directors for the Tempe Chamber of Commerce.


Jeffrey S. Mayhall
Executive Vice President

As Executive Vice President of Bollente Companies, Inc., Jeffrey Mayhall is actively involved in the execution of Bollente investments, financing, recapitalizations, acquisitions, sales and corporate compliance.
Most recently Mr. Mayhall founded and led Innovation Credit Corporation, an organization dedicated to financing, developing and marketing new innovative technologies and products. From 2006 – 2013, Mr. Mayhall served as the company’s President and grew Innovation Credit Corporation to become one of the largest international companies within its industry. Prior to founding Innovation Credit Corporation, Mr. Mayhall served as Director of Operations and General Counsel for a large commercial real estate development company.
Mr. Mayhall holds a bachelor’s degree in psychology from the University of Toledo and a Juris Doctorate from the University of Toledo, College of Law. After graduating from Law School, Mr. Mayhall relocated to Arizona where he was admitted to the Arizona Bar and became licensed in the United State District Court, District of Arizona.


